aland by Office of Film & Literature Classification since it was deemed to be objectionable.[102] In May 2008 an edited version of the book was allowed for sale if sealed and an indication of the censorship classification was displayed. The book was initially restricted in Australia:[103] after review the 2007 edition was banned outright.[54][104][105]',102),(2439,'Peyton Place (1956)','1956','Banned in Canada from 1956–1958.[77]',65),(2440,'The Protocols of the Elders of Zion (1903)','1903','Banned in various libraries and many attempts to ban in various nations, as in Russia.[106]',103),(2441,'Përbindëshi (The Monster) (1965)','1965-1990','Banned for 25 years in Albania.[107]',65),(2442,'The Quran','','As with many holy books, the Quran has been subject to scrutiny and censorship at various points throughout history. Proposals and movements advocating outright bans of the Quran are uncommon in the West, occurring only among extremist right-wing circles.[108]The most notable recent (and controversial) ban of a version of the Quran happened in 2013 when a Russian court censored the text under the country\'s \'extremism\' laws.[109]',71),(2443,'Rangila Rasul (1927)','1927','Currently banned in India, Pakistan, and Bangladesh.[110]',104),(2444,'Rights of Man (1791)','1791','Banned in the UK and author charged with treason for supporting the French Revolution.[23] Banned in Tsarist Russia after theDecembrist revolt.[111]',105),(2445,'Rowena Goes Too Far(1931)','1931','Banned in Australia because of customs belief that it \"lacked sufficient claim to the literary to excuse the obscenity\"[112]',65),(2446,'The Satanic Verses(1988)','1988','Banned in the following countries for alleged blasphemy against Islam: Bangladesh, Egypt, India, Iran, Kenya, Kuwait, Liberia, Malaysia, Papua New Guinea, Pakistan, Senegal, Singapore, Sri Lanka, Tanzania and Thailand.[113][114]',65),(2447,'The Satanic Bible(1969)','1969','Banned during apartheid in South Africa from 1973 to 1993 for moral reasons.[115]',71),(2448,'Schindler\'s Ark (1982)','1982','Banned in Lebanon for its positive depiction of Jews.[3]',65),(2449,'Scouting for the Reaper(2014)','2014','Banned in Eritrea in 2014 for its criticism of civil liberties under President Isaias Afewerki[57][not in citation given]',82),(2450,'Sexual Customs (\"Xing Fengsu\") (1989)','1989','Banned in China in 1989 for insulting Islam[116][117][118][119][120][121][122][123][124][125][126][127][128]',70),(2451,'Shivaji – Hindu King in Islamic India (2003)','2003','Banned in Indian state of Maharashtra in 2004 for \"promoting social enmity\"; ban overturned by Bombay High Court in 2007.[129]',84),(2452,'Smash and Grab: Annexation of Sikkim(1984)','1984','Banned in India. Describes the process of the annexation of the Buddhist kingdom of Sikkim by the Indian government of Indira Gandhi in 1975.[94]',84),(2453,'A Sneaking Suspicion(1995)','1995','Banned by the New South Wales Department of Education and Communities from state schools May 5, 2015 for undisclosed reasons. It was speculated that the book\'s pro-monogamy stance may have led to the ban.[130] The ban was lifted May 19, 2015.',71),(2454,'Snorri the Seal (1941)','1941','Satirical book banned during the German occupation of Norway.[131]',106),(2455,'Soft Target: How the Indian Intelligence Service Penetrated Canada (1989)','1989','Banned in India.[132]',107),(2456,'Sophie\'s Choice (1979)','1979','Banned in Lebanon for its positive depiction of Jews.[3]',65),(2457,'A Spoon on Earth','','Banned for distribution within the South Korean military as one of 23 books banned there beginning on August 2008.[14][133]',65),(2458,'Spycatcher (1985)','1985','Banned in the UK 1985–1988 for revealing secrets. Wright was a former MI5 intelligence officer and his book was banned before it was even published in 1987.[134][135]',81),(2459,'Storytellers II','','Withdrawn from print in Yugoslavia in 1964 because it contained stories by Dragiša Vasić.[30]',80),(2460,'The 